description.p:
Some examples of scheduling rules include, but are not limited to:
1) If the shipment is scheduled but not yet in transit then i) update once a day if the shipment is 2 or more days away from shipping; ii) else update once per 6 hours;
2) If the shipment is in transit then update once per hour;
3) If the shipment is out for delivery then update once per 15 minutes;
4) If the shipment is delivered then do not update.
